## Technical Specifications

Data Models: [Schema details]
- User { id: string, name: string, email: string, status: 'active'|'suspended', orgId: string, roles: string[], lastActiveAt: string | null }
- Org { id: string, name: string, ssoEnabled: boolean, dataPolicyId?: string, tenantSettings: any }
- Role { id: string, name: string, permissions: string[] }
- Integration { id: string, type: string, config: any, health: 'ok'|'warn'|'error', lastSyncAt?: string }
- ComplianceAudit { id: string, orgId: string, userId: string, action: string, timestamp: string, dataScope: string }
- CronJob { id: string, name: string, enabled: boolean, schedule: string, timezone: string, triggerType: 'time'|'event'|'conditional', target: string, inputPayload: any, permissions: string, constraints: any, safetyRails: any, retryPolicy: { backoffMs: number, maxAttempts: number }, outputs: any }
- Subscription { id: string, orgId: string, plan: string, status: string, startDate: string, endDate?: string, nextBillingDate?: string }
- Invoice { id: string, orgId: string, date: string, amount: number, status: string, lineItems: any[] }
- AuditLog { id: string, orgId: string, userId: string, action: string, timestamp: string, resource: string, changes?: any }

API Endpoints: [Routes and methods]
- Admin Users
  - GET /api/admin/users
  - POST /api/admin/users
  - PUT /api/admin/users/:id
  - DELETE /api/admin/users/:id
  - POST /api/admin/users/:id/activate
  - POST /api/admin/users/:id/reset-password
- Organizations
  - GET /api/admin/orgs
  - POST /api/admin/orgs
  - PUT /api/admin/orgs/:id
- Roles
  - GET /api/admin/roles
  - POST /api/admin/roles
  - PUT /api/admin/roles/:id
  - DELETE /api/admin/roles/:id
- Integrations
  - GET /api/admin/integrations
  - POST /api/admin/integrations
  - PUT /api/admin/integrations/:id
- Compliance & Audit
  - GET /api/admin/compliance/audits
  - POST /api/admin/compliance/export
  - GET /api/admin/compliance/exports/:id/logs
- Billing
  - GET /api/admin/billing/subscriptions
  - GET /api/admin/billing/invoices
  - POST /api/admin/billing/invoices/{id}/pay
- Cronjobs
  - GET /api/admin/cronjobs
  - POST /api/admin/cronjobs
  - POST /api/admin/cronjobs/:id/trigger
  - GET /api/admin/cronjobs/:id/runs
- Reports
  - GET /api/admin/reports
  - POST /api/admin/reports/generate
- Common
  - POST /api/auth/refresh-token
  - GET /api/auth/me (for authorization checks)

Security: Authentication & Authorization
- Role-based access control (RBAC) with admin/super-admin scopes.
- Ensure sensitive actions require approvals when configured (Approvals queue).
- Input validation on server; sanitize and enforce schema contracts.
- Audit trails for all admin actions; ensure immutable run artifacts.

Validation: Input and Response
- Client: Always validate API responses; use defaults like Array.isArray(data?.items) ? data.items : [].
- Backend: Validate payloads with explicit schemas; enforce required fields; return consistent shapes.
- All optional fields accessed with optional chaining.

Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All admin pages render correctly with proper navigation and responsive behavior across devices.
- [ ] All lists (users, orgs, roles, integrations, cronjobs) guard array operations and handle empty states without crashes.
- [ ] CRUD operations for users, orgs, roles, and integrations succeed with proper validation and audit logging.
- [ ] Cronjobs can be created, scheduled, triggered, and show per-run details; approvals flow functions as configured.
- [ ] Compliance exports generate artifacts, logs available, and downloads succeed.
- [ ] Billing dashboards reflect real subscription/invoice data with correct spend controls.
- [ ] Analytics dashboards render charts with correct color palette and accessible labeling.
- [ ] All endpoints are protected, return proper error messages, and do not leak sensitive data.

UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project's design system:
- Maintain the dark UI aesthetic with the specified color palette.
- Use Inter (or similar) for typography with the given weights and sizing.
- Follow 8px baseline grid; ensure gutter between content and sidebar is 220–260px.
- Card components: 8–12px radius; gradient background from #0B0B0C to #151718; subtle inner highlight; hover lift and border tint.
- Navigation: left rail with active state pill in #FF3B30; nested collapsible sections with carets.
- Data viz: low-contrast axes; teal/amber/purple accents; rounded corners on bars; tooltips with white text on dark panels.
- UI interactions: motion ranges 120–200ms; focus outlines on interactive elements; accessible hover/focus states.
- Use descriptive microcopy; ensure actions have clear undo/redo or confirmation where critical.

Visual Style
Imitate the provided color palette, typography, spacing, and design elements. Implement the exact token usage (colors, borders, radii, shadows) and maintain consistency across all admin sub-pages and components.

Gradients, borders, and shadows
- Card background: gradient from #111213 to #1A1A1B
- Borders: rgba(255,255,255,0.03)
- Shadows: elevation ~0 6px 18px rgba(0,0,0,0.6)

Key Design Elements recap
- Card hierarchy: icon/top region, bold title, metadata/subtitle below
- Sidebar: compact icon list with collapsible sections
- Data Visualization: muted gridlines, bright data series with rounded strokes
- Interactive elements: consistent, accessible button and input styles
- Badges & status indicators: subtle gray or accent red (#FF3B30) for alerts

Mandatory Coding Standards — Runtime Safety
- Supabase-like results handling: use data ?? [] wherever results might be null.
- Array operations guarded: (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : [].
- useState defaults: useState<Type[]>([]) for all arrays.
- API response shapes: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
- Optional chaining: use obj?.property?.nested when accessing nested data.
- Destructuring with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}.

Generate the complete, detailed prompt now:
- Create a comprehensive, actionable development prompt that an AI development tool can use to build the Admin Dashboard with all the components, pages, and features described above.
- Ensure the prompt includes all sections, data models, endpoints, authentication, UI guidelines, and acceptance criteria, and enforces the runtime safety requirements in every code artifact.

=== SUCCESS CRITERIA ===
# Success Criteria Checklist

## Code Quality

### TypeScript
- [ ] No TypeScript errors (`tsc --noEmit` passes)
- [ ] All functions and components have proper type definitions
- [ ] No `any` types used (use `unknown` if type is truly unknown)
- [ ] Props interfaces defined for all components
- [ ] API responses have type definitions

### Code Standards
- [ ] All imports use path aliases (@/ prefix)
- [ ] Components follow the established naming convention
- [ ] Files are organized in correct directories
- [ ] No unused imports or variables
- [ ] Consistent code formatting

## Component Implementation

### UI Components
- [ ] Use shadcn/ui components (Button, Card, Input, etc.) instead of building from scratch
- [ ] All interactive elements have hover states
- [ ] Components use the `cn()` utility for class merging
- [ ] Proper TypeScript props interfaces defined
- [ ] Components are responsive (mobile, tablet, desktop)

### Animations
- [ ] Motion library used for all animations (NOT framer-motion)
- [ ] Page transitions implemented with fade/slide
- [ ] Interactive elements have whileHover/whileTap animations
- [ ] List items use stagger animations where appropriate
- [ ] Animations respect `prefers-reduced-motion`

### Icons
- [ ] Lucide React icons used consistently
- [ ] Icons have consistent sizing (h-4 w-4, h-5 w-5, h-6 w-6)
- [ ] Icon colors match design system (text-primary, text-muted-foreground)

## Data Management

### React Query
- [ ] All data fetching uses React Query hooks
- [ ] Query keys follow the established pattern
- [ ] Mutations invalidate related queries
- [ ] Loading and error states handled
- [ ] Optimistic updates implemented where appropriate

### Forms
- [ ] Forms use react-hook-form
- [ ] Validation uses Zod schemas
- [ ] Error messages display properly
- [ ] Form submission shows loading state
- [ ] Success/error feedback via toast notifications

### API Layer
- [ ] API functions in src/api/ directory
- [ ] Axios used for HTTP requests
- [ ] Proper error handling with try/catch
- [ ] Auth tokens handled by interceptors
- [ ] Type-safe API function signatures

## User Experience

### Notifications
- [ ] Sonner toasts used for all notifications
- [ ] Success actions show success toast
- [ ] Errors show descriptive error messages
- [ ] Loading states show toast.loading()

### Loading States
- [ ] Skeleton loaders shown during data fetch
- [ ] Buttons show loading state during submission
- [ ] Disabled state applied during async operations

### Error Handling
- [ ] Network errors caught and displayed
- [ ] User-friendly error messages (no stack traces)
- [ ] Fallback UI for error states
- [ ] No unhandled promise rejections

## Navigation

### Route Accessibility
- [ ] All pages have routes defined in router configuration
- [ ] Every page is accessible through navigation (menu, sidebar, or direct URL)
- [ ] Main pages (Dashboard, Home, Settings, etc.) accessible from primary navigation
- [ ] Secondary pages accessible through contextual navigation or direct links
- [ ] Deep-linked pages have breadcrumbs or back navigation
- [ ] 404/Not Found page implemented for invalid routes
- [ ] Protected routes have proper authentication checks
- [ ] Navigation state persists across page refreshes where appropriate

### Navigation UX
- [ ] Active route highlighted in navigation menu
- [ ] Clear visual hierarchy in navigation structure
- [ ] Mobile navigation is accessible and usable
- [ ] Navigation items have hover/focus states
- [ ] Nested routes show parent-child relationships
- [ ] User can always return to main areas (Dashboard/Home)

## Styling

### Tailwind CSS
- [ ] Tailwind v3 classes used
- [ ] HSL color variables from design system
- [ ] Custom CSS properties used where defined
- [ ] Responsive breakpoints: mobile-first approach
- [ ] Dark mode support via CSS variables

### Design System
- [ ] Colors use theme variables (primary, secondary, accent)
- [ ] Spacing uses Tailwind scale (p-4, gap-6, etc.)
- [ ] Border radius uses theme values (rounded-lg)
- [ ] Shadows use theme values (shadow-card)
- [ ] Typography follows Inter font system

## Accessibility

- [ ] Semantic HTML elements used
